OL,5,EBIRDWATCHERS FLOCK TO WORLDWIDE WATCH  
OL,7,BYou don't have to be a bird expert to  
OL,8,Btake part in this year's World         
OL,9,EBirdwatch.BAn RSPB spokesman says:     
OL,10,B"This event is open to anyone who sees 
OL,11,Bbirds in their back yards or gardens.  
OL,13,B"TheyEdon't have to be rare.BBut it's a
OL,14,Bchance to speak to an expert about the 
OL,15,Bbirds and learn more about them."      
OL,16,B                                       
OL,17,BIf you don't know aEgolden orioleBfrom 
OL,18,BaEgoldfinch,Byou can phone the World   
OL,19,BBirdwatch hotline to find out.         
